Wednesday, 3 January 2018

Farewell 2017

   [39444512022_4c3956da66_z.jpg]
   This year's favourite...
   Places:
   • Valencia, Spain.
   • San Francisco, California.
   • Los Angeles, California.
   • Paris, always.
   Words:
   • Broflake: straight while male offended by any feminist or ethnic
   activity which is not directly designed for him.
   • Logophile: a lover of language, one who relishes the taste of words
   on the tongue & in the mind's eye.
   • Tsundoku: people who buy more books than they can actually read
   (Japanese).
   • Kalsarikännit: feeling when you are going to get drunk home alone in
   your underwear – with no intention of going out. (Finnish)
   Apps:
   • Podcast: Revisionist History by Malcolm Gladwell
   • Detour, guided walking tours.
   • Moment, put down your phone and get back to your life.
   Movies:
   • I Am Not Your Negro
   • Maudie
   • L'écume des jours
   Series:
   • American Crime Story: The People v. O.J. Simpson
   • Westworld
   • The Handmaid's Tale
   Music:
   • Masseduction by St. Vincent
   • Ibn El Leil by Mashrou' Leila
   • Petite Amie by Juliette Armanet
   Books:
   • On Tyranny: Twenty Lessons from the Twentieth Century by Timothy
   Snyder
   • Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind by Yuval Noah Harari
   • Dear Ijeawele, or a Feminist Manifesto in Fifteen Suggestions
   by Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie
   Small victories:
   • First time in Spain!
   • Visiting Yayoi Kusama's Infinity Room.
   • Getting my copy of Americanah signed by the magnificent Chimamanda
   Ngozi Adichie.
   •••
